LXCBENCH - Linux Containers Benchmarking
========================================

Among the different virtualization technologies Linux Containers (LXC)
are particularly appealing for implementing multi-hosting embedded systems,
by providing a userspace container object that supports full resource
isolation and resource control for an applications or a system.

The purpose of LXCBENCH GENIVI incubation project is to gain a better
understanding of the Linux Containers capabilities through benchmarking.

Home page: http://projects.genivi.org/lxcbench/

Mailing list: genivi-lxcbench@lists.genivi.org
- please use this list for all discussion: bug reports, enhancements, etc.
- archived at: http://lists.genivi.org/pipermail/genivi-lxcbench
- anyone is welcome to join the list; to do so, visit
  http://lists.genivi.org/mailman/listinfo/genivi-lxcbench

Patches are most welcome; if possible, please make them with diff -c and
include ChangeLog entries.

LXCBENCH is free software.  See the file COPYING for copying conditions.
